p: Of the 112 cat serum samples tested, 10 individuals (8.9%, 95% CI=3.5–14.29) were FeLV-positive; two individuals (1.7% 95% CI=0.07–4.2) were FIV-positive and one individual was CDV-serum neutralization positive, as a reciprocal titer of 1:160 (0.8%, 95% CI=0.08–2.6) ( Table 3). No coinfections or significant differences between ages, sex groups or areas were found related to positive status.
